Sales Analysis for an E-commerce Website¶

Project Overview:¶

  1. Data Exploration - Entity relationship diagrams
  2. Data Cleaning - Remove duplication and cleansing process
  3. Data Analysing - Answering the business questions
  4. Data Visualization - Matplot in python
  5. Documentation - jupyter notebook

Database Details:¶

  1. Customers: Contains information about the customers, including customer ID, first name, lastname,city, country phone and number.
  2. Products: Contains information about the products sold on the website, including product ID, product name, supplierid, package, isdisconnected and unitprice.
  3. Orders: Contains information about the orders placed by customers, including order ID, customer ID, order date, and total amount and order number.
  4. Order_Items: Contains information about the items included in each order, including order ID, product ID, quantity, and price

Project Tasks:¶

1. Data Exploration¶

This database has the detailed information about the Ecommerce websites with complete products, customer and order details.

2. Data Cleansing¶

Data cleansing process involved in this project are:

  1. Removing Duplicates
  2. Removing leading and trailing spaces
  3. Converting data types
  4. Handling missing values
  5. Standardizing values
  6. Handling outliers

Removing Duplicates¶

Cleansing process in [dbo].[Customer] table

  • Dropped the column name "supplierid" in customer table.
ALTER TABLE [dbo].[Customer] 
DROP COLUMN supplierid;

  • Combining the "FirstName" and "LastName" to get "FullName" to make sure the data integrity.
ALTER TABLE [dbo].[Customer] 
ADD FullName VARCHAR(100);

  • Concating the both values. [FirstName + LastName = FullName].
UPDATE [dbo].[Customer]
SET [FullName] = [FirstName] + ' ' +  [LastName];

  • Checking for duplicate values in the rows of all each columns.
1.
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Customer]
WHERE Id IN (
    SELECT Id
    FROM [dbo].[Customer]
    GROUP BY Id 
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

2. 
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Customer]
WHERE FullName IN (
    SELECT FullName
    FROM [dbo].[Customer]
    GROUP BY FullName 
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

3.
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Customer]
WHERE Phone IN (
    SELECT Phone
    FROM [dbo].[Customer]
    GROUP BY Phone 
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

Cleansing process in [dbo].[Order] table

  • Checked for duplicates in order table in ID and OrderNumber column
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Order]
WHERE id IN (
    SELECT id 
    FROM [dbo].[Order]
    GROUP BY id
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

DELETE FROM [dbo].[Order]
WHERE OrderNumber IN (
    SELECT OrderNumber 
    FROM [dbo].[Order]
    GROUP BY OrderNumber
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

Cleansing process in [dbo].[OrderItem] table

  • Checked for duplicates in orderitem table in ID column.
DELETE FROM [dbo].[OrderItem]
WHERE Id IN (
    SELECT Id
    FROM [dbo].[OrderItem]
    GROUP BY Id
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

Cleansing process in [dbo].[Product] table.

  • Checked for duplicates in Product table in ID column.
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Product]
WHERE Id IN (
    SELECT Id
    FROM [dbo].[Product]
    GROUP BY Id
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

DELETE FROM [dbo].[Product]
WHERE ProductName IN (
    SELECT ProductName
    FROM [dbo].[Product]
    GROUP BY ProductName
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
);

Note: Not supposed to perform remove duplicate in all column.
Example: CustomerId in Order table. Single customer can order multiple items so we can't perform this action.

Removing leading and trailing spaces¶

It will applicable all the columns so queried with common SQL commands

Example: Trimmed the FullName column and 91 rows got affected.

UPDATE [dbo].[Customer]
SET FullName = TRIM(FullName);

Converting data types¶

Checking and verifying the Data types of the all tables.

SELECT COLUMN_NAME, DATA_TYPE
FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS;

Verified that all columns of the tables has appropiate data types.

Handling missing values¶

  • Tables order and products has missing and null values.
  • In order table has FK_ORDERITE_REFERENCE_ORDER constraints.
  • STATUSS column is removed and 79 id in Product has empty values also deleted.

DELETE FROM [dbo].[Order]
WHERE STATUSS IS NULL; 
DELETE FROM [dbo].[Product]
WHERE Package = '';

Standardizing values¶

In customers table Country values are standarded.

UPDATE [dbo].[Customers]
SET Country = UPPER('USA')
WHERE Country = LOWER('usa')
UPDATE [dbo].[Customers]
SET Country = UPPER('UK')
WHERE Country = LOWER('uk')

Handling outliers¶

  • Note: No outliers is detected from this ecommerceDB database.

3. Data Analysing¶

Clients Requirements

1. What are the total sales revenue and the total number of orders for each month?

Analysis: Revenue and total orders are analysed from the [dbo].[Order]

Required result : Date, Total sales per month and Total no.of orders.

SQL Queries:

SELECT 
    FORMAT(OrderDate, 'yyyy-MM') AS 'Date by Month',
    SUM(TotalAmount) AS 'Total Revenue',
    COUNT(*) AS 'Number of Orders'
FROM
    [dbo].[Order]
GROUP BY
    FORMAT(OrderDate, 'yyyy-MM');

2. What are the top 5 best-selling products in terms of quantity and revenue?

Analysis: Revenue and total orders are analysed from the [dbo].[Order]

Required result: Date, Total sales per month and Total no.of orders.

SQL Queries:

SELECT
    TOP 5 P.ProductName, 
    OI.ProductId,
    SUM(OI.Quantity) AS 'Quantity', 
    SUM(O.TotalAmount) AS 'Revenue' 
FROM 
    [dbo].[Order] O
INNER JOIN
    [dbo].[OrderItem] OI ON OI.OrderId = O.Id 
INNER JOIN
    [dbo].[Product] P ON P.Id = OI.ProductId
GROUP BY
    P.ProductName, 
    OI.Quantity,
    OI.ProductId, O.Id
ORDER BY
    OI.Quantity DESC, 
    SUM(O.TotalAmount) DESC;

3. Who are the top 10 customers in terms of total spending?

Analysis: Total spending are analysed from the [dbo].[Order] and [dbo].[Customers]

Required result : Id, Customer Name and Total Amounts.

SQL Queries:

SELECT 
    TOP 10 C.Id,
    C.FullName AS 'Customer Name',
    SUM(O.TotalAmount) AS 'Total Amount' 
FROM
    [dbo].[Customers] C
INNER JOIN 
    [dbo].[Order] O ON O.CustomerId = C.Id
GROUP BY
     C.Id, C.FullName
ORDER BY
    SUM(O.TotalAmount) DESC;

4. What is the average order value for each month?

Analysis: Average order values are analysed from the [dbo].[Order]

Required result : Date by Month and Average Values.

SQL Queries:

SELECT 
    FORMAT(OrderDate, 'yyyy-MM') AS 'Date by Month',
    AVG(TotalAmount) AS 'Average Values'
FROM 
    [dbo].[Order]
GROUP BY 
    FORMAT(OrderDate, 'yyyy-MM');

5. What is the customer retention rate for the given period (e.g. month, quarter, year)?

Analysis: customer retention rate are analysed from the [dbo].[Order]

Required result : Date by Month and Average Values.

SQL Queries:

SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT retained_customers.CustomerID) AS RetainedCustomers,
    COUNT(DISTINCT all_customers.CustomerID) AS TotalCustomers,
    CASE WHEN COUNT(DISTINCT all_customers.CustomerID) > 0
         THEN CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT retained_customers.CustomerID) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(DISTINCT all_customers.CustomerID)
         ELSE 0
    END AS RetentionRate
FROM
    (
        SELECT CustomerID
        FROM [dbo].[Order]
        WHERE OrderDate >= @StartDate AND OrderDate <= @EndDate
    ) AS retained_customers
INNER JOIN
    (
        SELECT CustomerID
        FROM [dbo].[Order]
        WHERE OrderDate < @StartDate
    ) AS all_customers
ON retained_customers.CustomerID = all_customers.CustomerID;

6. Which category of products generates the highest revenue?

Analysis: highest revenue are analysed from the [dbo].[OrderItem] and [dbo].[Product]

Required result : ProductName and TotalRevenue.

SQL Queries:

SELECT
    TOP 1
    P.ProductName,
    SUM(OI.Quantity * OI.UnitPrice) AS TotalRevenue
FROM
    Product P
    INNER JOIN OrderItem OI ON P.ID = OI.ProductID
GROUP BY
    P.ProductName
ORDER BY
    TotalRevenue DESC;
